United States Consulate
Sierra Leone
7th October 1875

No. 3
Sir,

I have the honor to inform you, this Office has had no Flag since my appointment as Consul and that we have for the past three months been using one belonging to the American Bark "Tropic Bird" and as this vessel haves this part in a day or so the Captain has asked me to return his Flag Hill you please instruct the Department of State to furnish me with a moderate sired Flag oor two and oblige.

H. Hunter Esqre
Acting Secretary
H
I have the honor to be
Sir
Your most obedient servant
James France
Acting United S. Consul
France
